description: Lists all of the Amazon Managed Service for Prometheus workspaces in your account. This includes workspaces being created or deleted.

parameters.name: alias
parameters.description: If this is included, it filters the results to only the workspaces with names that start with the value that you specify here. Amazon Managed Service for Prometheus will automatically strip any blank spaces from the beginning and end of the alias that you specify.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: The token for the next set of items to return. You receive this token from a previous call, and use it to get the next page of results. The other parameters must be the same as the initial call. For example, if your initial request has maxResults of 10, and there are 12 workspaces to return, then your initial request will return 10 and a nextToken. Using the next token in a subsequent call will return the remaining 2 workspaces.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: A token indicating that there are more results to retrieve. You can use this token as part of your next ListWorkspaces request to retrieve those results.

nested_items.name: workspaces
nested_items.description: An array of WorkspaceSummary structures containing information about the workspaces requested.

nested_items.name: alias
nested_items.description: The alias that is assigned to this workspace to help identify it. It does not need to be unique.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that the workspace was created.

nested_items.name: kmsKeyArn
nested_items.description: (optional) If the workspace was created with a customer managed KMS key, the ARN for the key used.

nested_items.name: statusCode
nested_items.description: The current status of the workspace.

nested_items.name: workspaceId
nested_items.description: The unique ID for the workspace.
